  <h2 class=3D"name" style=3D"view-transition-name: ancestry-drakona-title;=
">
    Drakona</h2>
  <div style=3D"view-transition-name: ancestry-drakona-description;">
    Drakona resemble wingless dragons in humanoid form and possess a powerf=
ul elemental breath. All drakona have thick scales that provide excellent n=
atural armor against both attacks and the forces of nature. They are large =
in size, ranging from 5 feet to 7 feet on average, with long sharp teeth. N=
ew teeth grow throughout a Drakona=E2=80=99s approximately 350-year lifespa=
n, so they are never in danger of permanently losing an incisor. Unlike the=
ir dragon ancestors, drakona don=E2=80=99t have wings and can=E2=80=99t fly=
 without magical aid. Members of this ancestry pass down the element of the=
ir breath through generations, though in rare cases, a drakona=E2=80=99s el=
emental power will differ from the rest of their family=E2=80=99s.</div>

  <div>
    <h3>Features</h3>
          <p><strong>Scales:</strong> Your scales act as natural protection=
. When you would take Severe damage, you can **mark a Stress** to mark 1 fe=
wer Hit Points.</p>
              <p><strong>Elemental Breath:</strong> Choose an element for y=
our breath (such as electricity, fire, or ice). You can use this breath aga=
inst a target or group of targets within Very Close range, treating it as a=
n Instinct weapon that deals **d8** magic damage using your Proficiency.</p=
>
      </div>

  <div class=3D"actions">
