  <h2 class=3D"name" style=3D"view-transition-name: ancestry-firbolg-title;=
">
    Firbolg</h2>
  <div style=3D"view-transition-name: ancestry-firbolg-description;">
    Firbolgs are bovine humanoids typically recognized by their broad noses=
 and long, drooping ears. Some have faces that are a blend of humanoid and =
bison, ox, cow, or other bovine creatures. Others, often referred to as min=
otaurs, have heads that entirely resemble cattle. They are tall and muscula=
r creatures, with long tails ranging from around 3 feet to 7 feet, and poss=
ess remarkable strength no matter their age. Some firbolgs are known to use=
 this strength to charge their adversaries, an action that is particularly =
effective for those who have one of the many varieties of horn styles commo=
nly found in this ancestry. Though their unique characteristics can vary, a=
ll firbolgs are covered in fur, which can be muted and earth-toned in color=
, or come in a variety of pastels, such as soft pinks and blues. On average=
, firbolgs live for about 150 years.</div>

  <div>
    <h3>Features</h3>
          <p><strong>Charge:</strong> When you succeed on an Agility Roll t=
o move from Far or Very Far range into Melee range with one or more targets=
, you can **mark a Stress** to deal **1d12** physical damage to all targets=
 within Melee range.</p>
              <p><strong>Unshakable:</strong> When you would mark a Stress,=
 roll a **d6**. On a result of 6, don=E2=80=99t mark it.</p>
      </div>

  <div class=3D"actions">
