  <h2 class=3D"name" style=3D"view-transition-name: ancestry-orc-title;">
    Orc</h2>
  <div style=3D"view-transition-name: ancestry-orc-description;">
    Orcs are humanoids most easily recognized by their square features and =
boar-like tusks that protrude from their lower jaw. Tusks come in various s=
izes, and though they extend from the mouth, they aren=E2=80=99t used for c=
onsuming food. Instead, many orcs choose to decorate their tusks with signi=
ficant ornamentation. Orcs typically live for 125 years, and unless altered=
, their tusks continue to grow throughout the course of their lives. Their =
ears are pointed, and their hair and skin typically have green, blue, pink,=
 or gray tones. Orcs tend toward a muscular build, and their average height=
 ranges from 5 feet to 6 =C2=BD feet.</div>

  <div>
    <h3>Features</h3>
          <p><strong>Sturdy:</strong> When you have 1 Hit Point remaining, =
attacks against you have disadvantage.</p>
              <p><strong>Tusks:</strong> When you succeed on an attack agai=
nst a target within Melee range, you can **spend a Hope** to gore the targe=
t with your tusks, dealing an extra **1d6** damage.</p>
      </div>

  <div class=3D"actions">
    <a href=3D"https://daggerheart.org/reference/ancestries/orc">
      Read more</a>
  </div>
</div>
